<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Vim on Barim's blog · ابراهيم</title><link>https://barim.us/tags/vim/</link><description>Recent content in Vim on Barim's blog · ابراهيم</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Tue, 14 Jan 2025 18:17:46 +0100</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://barim.us/tags/vim/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Convert multiple files to utf8 using vim</title><link>https://barim.us/post/2014-12-03-convert-multiple-files-to-utf8-using-vim/</link><pubDate>Wed, 03 Dec 2014 18:44:07 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://barim.us/post/2014-12-03-convert-multiple-files-to-utf8-using-vim/</guid><description>&lt;p>The fastest and more efficient way to batch multiple files encoding conversion :&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:2;-o-tab-size:2;tab-size:2;">&lt;code class="language-sh" data-lang="sh">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>vim +&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#34;argdo se fileencoding=utf-8 | w | bnext&amp;#34;&lt;/span> +&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#34;q&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">`&lt;/span> find . -type f -name &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#34;*.rsp&amp;#34;&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;p>+&amp;ldquo;argdo&amp;rdquo; : execute the following vim commands for each file (filencode, save and next buffer)&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>